                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d499">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.731/132: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-09T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 9, 1939—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1204. Department’s 1157, October 4, 8 p.m. It is imperative that Department be
                    advised at earliest possible moment in what cases if any French telegraphic
                    administration accepts messages in the codes specified in your telegram 2203.
                    Present uncertainty is highly detrimental both to companies and American users.
                    Please endeavor to reply to Department’s 1157 within a day or two.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
